{"id":"chapiter","term":"Chapiter","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The ornamental head or capital of a pillar. Three Hebrew words are so rendered. (1.) <em>Cothereth</em> (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 7:16\">1 Kings 7:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 25:17\">2 Kings 25:17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 4:12\">2 Chr. 4:12</a>), meaning a “diadem” or “crown.” (2.) <em>Tzepheth</em> (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 3:15\">2 Chr. 3:15</a>). (3.) <em>Rosh</em> (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 36:38\">Ex. 36:38</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:17\">38:17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:19\">19</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 38:28\">28</a>), properly a “head” or “top.”</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Kings 7:16","2 Kings 25:17","2 Chronicles 4:12","2 Chronicles 3:15","Exodus 36:38","Exodus 38:17","Exodus 38:19","Exodus 38:28"]}